# Orrery — Cursor rule

The canonical agent-instruction file for this repo is **[AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md)** at the repo root. It's tool-agnostic and applies to Cursor, Claude Code, and any other coding agent equally — read it before touching any file.

For any task that crosses one file, also read **[`docs/adr/TA.md`](../../docs/adr/TA.md)** — the single-page architecture map (v2.0, current as of v0.6.0). It documents every route, subsystem, 3D scene, asset pipeline, contract, and constraint with the ADR that locked it.

This rule exists so Cursor surfaces the universal contract automatically. There are no Cursor-specific deviations from AGENTS.md; if you need to add one in the future, put it below this line so the single source of truth in AGENTS.md stays clean.

